Sentencas: Two methods of current collection/interconnection are developed for a novel tubular design solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Cathode current-collectors for a novel tubular SOFC design

Sentencas: Nimonic 90 wires, coated with LaCoO3-delta are used as the cathode current-collectors.
Titulo: Cathode current-collectors for a novel tubular SOFC design

Sentencas: When compared with the uncoated Nimonic wires, the LaCoO3-delta perovskite coated Nimonic wires improve the current densities of the cells.
Titulo: Cathode current-collectors for a novel tubular SOFC design

Sentencas: The latter is attributed to the fact that the coating improves the electrical contact between the wire and the cathode.
Titulo: Cathode current-collectors for a novel tubular SOFC design

Sentencas: The second method of current collection, whereby silver inks are painted on to the surface of the cathodes and then fired in situ, achieves greater cell performances than the Nimonic 90 wire systems.
Titulo: Cathode current-collectors for a novel tubular SOFC design

Sentencas: At 900 degrees C and 0.7 V, with 3-cm long cathodes, a current density of 0.20 A cm(-2) is achieved for cells with silver strip current-collectors.
Titulo: Cathode current-collectors for a novel tubular SOFC design
